Boral (without aluminum cladding)
Materials.References: Reactor Handbook, Vol. 1: composition from Table 51.28 and density from Table 51.29.  Boral is a mixture of B4C and aluminum; alloy is held in aluminum cladding 0.020 in thick, with which the material is brittle and difficult to handle; the B4C conent in the alloy can be as high as 50%; imputiries less than 1%; major impurity is iron.

Materials.Name: Boral (with aluminum cladding, 1/4 in. sheet)
Materials.References: Reactor Handbook, Vol. 1: composition from Table 51.28 and density from Table 51.29.  Elemental composition summed to 100.2% and was renormalized.  Boral is a mixture of B4C and aluminum; alloy is held in aluminum cladding 0.020 in thick, with which the material is brittle and difficult to handle; the B4C conent in the alloy can be as high as 50%; imputiries less than 1%; major impurity is iron.
